# Release signing for Tally.
#
# 1. Generate an upload keystore (do this ONCE, keep it safe & backed up):
#
#    keytool -genkeypair -v -storetype PKCS12 \
#      -keystore tally-upload.keystore \
#      -alias tally-upload -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000
#
# 2. Put the keystore file somewhere OUTSIDE the repo (never commit it).
#
# 3. Add these to android/gradle.properties (or ~/.gradle/gradle.properties), NOT committed:
#
# TALLY_UPLOAD_STORE_FILE=/absolute/path/to/tally-upload.keystore
# TALLY_UPLOAD_STORE_PASSWORD=your-store-password
# TALLY_UPLOAD_KEY_ALIAS=tally-upload
# TALLY_UPLOAD_KEY_PASSWORD=your-key-password
#
# With these present, `npm run bundle:android` produces a release AAB signed with your
# upload key. Without them, release builds fall back to the debug key (local testing only).
